by flashytonystark

“Mr. Stark?”

“How many times do I have to tell you that it’s okay to call me Tony?”

Peter at least has the decency to look sheepish at this and shrugs. “Sorry… Tony. Anyway, I know your wedding to Miss. Po—Pepper—is coming up soon and I know you told me Michelle can come as my date, which I’m super thankful for, like super-super thankful, but I was wondering… like… I dunno, could you…?”

“Peter, I have absolutely no idea where you’re going with this or what you’re asking me to do. You gotta give me something here, kid.”

“Canyouteachmehowtodance?”

summary: Secret Mission Teaser
title: Secret Mission Teaser
body:
A/n: a new Peter Parker series I’ve been working on 

“Don’t you do it,” Y/n grumbled, glancing at the boy currently focused on her. She turned her attention back to the window as she returned to her sulking. Her plan had ended up as a bust and if that weren’t enough she could already feel the lecture Tony and the others were about to give her. Tears pricked the back of her eyes, threatening to come out. “Stop,” her voice cracked as she warned Peter again.

“I’m not even doing anything.”

She could hear the smile in his voice, the way his voice became more boyish due to him knowing exactly what he was doing. Despite herself, Y/n turned to face him once again and was greeted by his cheeky wholesome smile. She muttered to herself, trying to hide the smile teasing her lips, “I hate you.”

Peter’s laugh replaced the dense awkward air hanging over them, “just like how you hate Spider-Man.” He wrapped his arm around Y/n’s shoulders, pulling her into his side. “If it makes you feel better, you look amazing tonight- and every day for that matter. You looked a lot better than that Fisk guy.” Y/n finally let out a laugh as she buried her face in his side, causing his smile to grow wider. “And I bet you could’ve kicked his ass..” he trailed off once he noticed Tony paying attention to them with a smirk on his face.

Part 1

summary: You know something? If you DO decide to make that sequel, it might be interesting to see the aftermath of Tony and Steve finally...
question: You know something? If you DO decide to make that sequel, it might be interesting to see the aftermath of Tony and Steve finally having that common ground of doing ANYTHING for the sake of one person (Peter and Bucky, respectively). Meanwhile, off in the corner or in another room somewhere, Peter and Bucky are complaining to each other about how overprotective Tony and Steve have gotten with them, so they just run off to get away from their mothering and have fun. XD
answer:
GET OUT OF MY HEAD!!!!!!!!!!

.

.

.

.

(Seriously though. The entire focus point of Identity Theft was Tony struggling to accept Peter as a son-figure and himself as a father figure. My plan would be to make the sequel the other perspective: Peter struggling to accept Tony as a father figure, especially with his over protectiveness and insistance to stay out of a certain OsCorp situtation which: spoiler alert, he doesn’t. Bucky being around totally brings in that shared annoyance of the over protectiveness AND they’re both dealing with PTSD and….get the hell out of my head!!)

summary: Can I have a Dolan twin, harry potter and marvel ship? I'm 5'7, I have hair just like yours and tan skin. I love reading,...
question: Can I have a Dolan twin, harry potter and marvel ship? I'm 5'7, I have hair just like yours and tan skin. I love reading, singing and watching movies. Thank you!
answer:
You’d be a friend to the twins.

The boys love to call you when they want to have a good time, whether it be a movie you talk about non stop and they actually can’t wait to see or a visit to a karaoke night where they willingly humiliate themselves to make you laugh if you feel bad. Grayson would beg you to show him how to braid your hair for future need and Ethan would snap it all to make fun of his brother who is actually really skilled.

I’d ship you with Luna Lovegood.

Most people stay away from her or tend to tease her for her peculiarities, but not you. You’ve always been protective of Luna, hexing those who dared say anything mean to the girl. She’d reciprocate by sharing her favorite books with you, just spending some quality time together. You’d have your own spot in the library, just by the window, where you could talk to her until it was time for bed. Whenever you needed her, Luna was there as she’s loyal and brave when it comes to protecting those she cares for.

I’d ship you with Peter Parker.

Peter is such a goof, a perfect guy to go to when you wanna have a good laugh. While he’s great to talk to and do school work with, he’s also a great to do something fun with. After all, you figured out his secret pretty quickly and ever since, you’ve been his close friend. He’d use his webs to safely give you a feel of what it means to fly and he’d never once jeopardize your life, meaning he’d often leave you someplace to deal with the perpetrators himself. The only downside is being constantly worried if he’ll get hurt or patching him up when it does happen.
